<DocsLayout title="Documentation">
  <p class="doc-eyebrow">// docs</p>

  <h1>Portefaix Documentation</h1>

  <p>
    Portefaix is a complete, open-source platform engineering toolkit for building production-grade
    Kubernetes platforms on any cloud. These docs cover every layer of the stack — from bootstrapping
    infrastructure with Terraform, to applying GitOps with ArgoCD, to enforcing policies
    with Kyverno and OPA.
  </p>

  <h2>Platform Sub-projects</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Sub-project</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Repository</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>portefaix-kubernetes</strong></td>
        <td>Production Kubernetes configurations: operators, GitOps, observability.</td>
        <td><a href="https://github.com/portefaix/portefaix-kubernetes" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub ↗</a></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>portefaix-infrastructure</strong></td>
        <td>Terraform modules for cloud infrastructure across AWS, GCP, Azure, and more.</td>
        <td><a href="https://github.com/portefaix/portefaix-infrastructure" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub ↗</a></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>portefaix-hub</strong></td>
        <td>Curated Helm charts optimised for the Portefaix platform.</td>
        <td><a href="https://github.com/portefaix/portefaix-hub" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub ↗</a></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>portefaix-policies</strong></td>
        <td>OPA/Rego and Kyverno policies for security, compliance, and governance.</td>
        <td><a href="https://github.com/portefaix/portefaix-policies" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub ↗</a></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  {sections.map((s) => (
    <>
      <h2>{s.label}</h2>
      <ul>
        {s.items.map((item) => (
          <li>
            <a href={item.href}>{item.title}</a> — {item.desc}
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </>
  ))}

  <h2>Design Principles</h2>

  <p>
    Portefaix is built on a set of core engineering principles that guide every decision across
    all sub-projects:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>GitOps-first</strong> — infrastructure and application state is declared in Git and reconciled automatically.</li>
    <li><strong>Policy-as-code</strong> — security and compliance requirements are encoded as machine-checkable policies.</li>
    <li><strong>Cloud-agnostic</strong> — the same abstractions work across AWS, GCP, Azure, and on-premises environments.</li>
    <li><strong>Observable by default</strong> — metrics, logs, and traces are built in, not bolted on.</li>
    <li><strong>Open standards</strong> — built on CNCF projects, OpenTelemetry, and open specifications.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="callout callout-info">
    <p>
      <strong>Getting started?</strong> Begin with the <a href="/docs/guides/gitops/">GitOps Principles</a> guide
      to understand the foundational model, then pick your cloud provider under Infrastructure.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="callout callout-warn">
    <p>
      <strong>FluxCD is deprecated</strong> as of Portefaix v2.0.0. ArgoCD is the recommended GitOps engine going forward.
      The FluxCD guide is preserved for reference at <a href="/docs/guides/fluxcd/">docs/guides/fluxcd</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
